The tangent function \(\tan x\) oscillates between negative and positive infinity as \(x\) goes to infinity. The function \(f(x)\) is continuous and decreasing in the interval \((0, \frac{\pi}{2})\) and increasing in the interval \((\frac{\pi}{2}, \frac{3\pi}{2})\). This behavior suggests that the function \(f(x)\) will have solutions in the intervals \((0, \frac{\pi}{2})\) and \((\frac{\pi}{2}, \frac{3\pi}{2})\).

