The 200th smallest solution in the interval \((0, \frac{\pi}{2})\) can be approximated by finding the 200th smallest value in the sequence of positive solutions of the equation \(x - \frac{\pi}{2} = \tan x\). This can be done by using numerical methods or approximations, but for the purpose of this problem, we can use the fact that the 200th smallest positive solution is approximately \(\frac{\pi}{2} - \frac{1}{200}\).

